The Senior Special Assistant to the President on Media and Publicity, Mallam Garba Shehu, has started following the Tinubu Media Support Group on Twitter. Shehu, who was among the first presidential spokesmen to tweet after the Twitter ban was lifted on January 13, has been active ever since. The presidential spokesman, who joined the microblogging site in April 2015, follows 365 other Twitter users and has over 1.2 million followers. The Tinubu Media Support Group (TMS), @TinubuMediaS, was opened in January following the declaration of the Lagos Governor, Bola Tinubu to contest the presidential ticket of the ruling All Progressive Congress (APC).   Delta APC publicity secretary resigns, leaves party     Time has come to choose wisely     Osun 2022: Adeleke family bickers over PDP ticket   - Advertisement - The profile of the group describes it as “Volunteer Media Support, BAT Fans, Promoters of BAT’23 project.” So far, the group follows 455 Twitter users and has 954 followers, including the presidential spokesman. President Muhammadu Buhari has refrained from disclosing his choice of successor, saying recently he would rather keep it to himself to prevent the individual from being “eliminated.” When pressed in a recent television interview on whether he has any favourite in the APC to take over, he added: “No. I wouldn’t because he may be eliminated if I mention it. I better keep it secret”.